osdi:events.description: Starbucks partners across the country will be going on strike on Red Cup Day - Starbucks’ biggest sales day of the year - to protest unfair labor practices, and are asking allies to stand alongside them in solidarity. They need your help to continue to demand Starbucks respect the workers demands and stop the egregious union busting tactics.
osdi:events.title: Starbucks Workers Union Red Cup Rebellion
osdi:events.instructions: Meet in front of Starbucks on 4094 18th St, San Francisco to rally and show solidarity for our comrades working at Starbucks. Signs, water, and snacks will be provided.

osdi:events.description:
On Sunday, 11/19 join us for a flyering event to raise awareness for EWOC! The Emergency Workplace Organizing Committee (EWOC) is a project of the Democratic Socialists of America (DSA) and the United Electrical, Radio and Machine Workers of America (UE) to build a distributed, grassroots organizing program to support workers organizing at the workplace. We are planning to target businesses that are good candidates for unionization. Meet us at the DSA office (1916 McAllister) at 1 pm. We will target the areas around the office (Haight, Panhandle, etc) but encourage folks to take flyers and spread the word.

The goal of this event is to spread awareness to workers about organizing their workplace!
osdi:events.title: Emergency Workplace Organizing Committee + DSA SF Flyering Event
osdi:events.instructions: Thanks for RSVPing!

osdi:events.description:
Join SF City College workers and students who are rallying outside the Board of Trustees meeting to demand the district provide living wages and commit to reasonable classes sizes. At a time when the district’s own finance team shows a $9MM surplus, it is egregious to require workers and students to shoulder the rising costs of living and a decreased quality of their education.

Date: Thursday, Oct 26th @ 5pm

Location: 55 Frida Kahlo Way, in front of East entrance of MUB building, Ocean Campus

location.venue: Multi-Use Building on Ocean Campus at City College of San Francisco

osdi:events.title: Thurs. Oct 26, Rally with City College workers & students

osdi:events.description:
On Monday, 9/18, join us at 555 Franklin St. from 4pm to 8pm to stand with SF teachers !

San Francisco educators are organizing for raises, improved working conditions, fully staffed schools, student supports, and protection from poor management decisions. Take action with us and come support the bargaining team. We will be picketing outside the bargaining meeting on Monday from 4pm-8pm - there are two 'shifts' for early and late release school sites, but you can ignore those - please come for any period of time you can make it for  !
osdi:events.title: 9/18 SF Teachers Picket for a Fair Contract
osdi:events.instructions: Check in at the table, grab a sign, and thank you!

osdi:events.description:
Building on our past sessions on class composition and the rank-and-file union model, this month we are going to practice talking to your coworkers. We’ll be meeting Thursday 6/29 from 6:30pm to 8:00pm, at 1916 McAllister.


We will be expanding on what we’ve learned so far by practicing organizing 1-on-1 conversations with each other. The 1-on-1 is the essential building block of any organizing campaign, and by practicing it we can prepare for the campaigns at our workplaces. Please RSVP here! dsasf.org/tech-workers-meet
osdi:events.title: Tech Worker Meetup June 2023
osdi:events.instructions: Join us at 6:30 at the office and sign in using the printed out QR codes
